{
  "dialogueGraphs": [
    {
      "id": "DG_SCN061_APERTURE_BAY_MIRROR_SURFACE",
      "sceneId": "SCN-061",
      "startNodeId": "N001_INTRO",
      "nodes": [
        {
          "id": "N001_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "Aperture Bay is lit like a loading dock that got promoted.\n\nThe aperture is a mirror-surface circle set into a frame that insists it is just another piece of municipal infrastructure.\n\nA floor mark\u2014RADIO SWEET-SPOT\u2014is painted where your boots already are, as if the building is trying to keep you from wandering into interpretation.",
          "next": "N010_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N010_MAIN_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_APERTURE",
              "text": "look: Mirror-surface aperture.",
              "next": "N100_APERTURE_DESC"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_SHROUD",
              "text": "look: Control shroud label.",
              "next": "N200_SHROUD_DESC"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_SWEETSPOT",
              "text": "look: Radio sweet-spot floor mark.",
              "next": "N300_SWEETSPOT_DESC"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_CHUTE",
              "text": "look: Outgoing packet chute.",
              "next": "N400_CHUTE_DESC"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_SHOW_TUNE",
              "text": "show: Tune the bay speaker grille for cleaner bleed-through.",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "skill",
                  "skill": "PROCEDURE",
                  "dc": 12
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N060_TUNE_PASS",
              "onFailNext": "N061_TUNE_FAIL"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_INIT_REVERSE",
              "text": "use: Initiate reverse routing correction.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act2.slotTokenCollected",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "next": "N480_CONFIRM_INTRO"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_INIT_REVERSE_NO_TOKEN",
              "text": "use: Initiate reverse routing correction.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act2.slotTokenCollected",
                  "op": "!=",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "next": "N590_NO_TOKEN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE",
              "text": "leave: Step away.",
              "next": "N900_END_LEAVE"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN",
          "type": "redirect",
          "target": "N010_MAIN_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N060_TUNE_PASS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You press a thumb against the grille, adjust the angle by millimeters, and listen the way you listen for a bearing going bad.\n\nThe hiss changes.\n\nNot a channel. Not a call. Just cleaner bleed\u2014enough to confirm there is a world on the other side that would prefer not to be confirmed.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N061_TUNE_FAIL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You try to coax clarity out of the grille. It gives you the same exhausted hiss.\n\nIf there's a signal, it's not volunteering.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N100_APERTURE_DESC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The surface reflects you with the accuracy of an inspection mirror.\n\nThen it reflects you from an angle you are not standing at.\n\nThe frame has three sets of bolt heads with three different paint codes, like three different crews tried to agree without meeting.",
          "next": "N110_APERTURE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N110_APERTURE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_NORMAL",
              "text": "ask: Normal?",
              "next": "N120_APERTURE_NORMAL_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_SEAM",
              "text": "look: Check the frame seam.",
              "next": "N130_APERTURE_SEAM_NARR"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the bay options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N120_APERTURE_NORMAL_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Normal?",
          "next": "N121_APERTURE_NORMAL_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N121_APERTURE_NORMAL_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The mirror does not answer.\n\nThe bay\u2019s status panel continues to display NORMAL OPERATION in a font that predates doubt.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N130_APERTURE_SEAM_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The seam is clean. Too clean.\n\nSomeone has been here with solvent and a sense of liability.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N200_SHROUD_DESC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The control shroud has a laminated label zip-tied to it like a confession that refuses to be stapled.\n\nIt reads:\n\n\u201cSPINDLE NODE INTERFACE \u2014 ALIGNMENT LOCK CONTROL\u201d\n\u201cCAUTION: DO NOT INTERRUPT LOCK WITHOUT ROUTING INSTRUMENTS\u201d\n\nThe word \u201crouting\u201d is underlined once, carefully, like it\u2019s the only word anyone can defend.",
          "next": "N210_SHROUD_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N210_SHROUD_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_INSTRUMENTS",
              "text": "ask: What instruments.",
              "next": "N220_SHROUD_INSTRUMENTS_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_SERVICETAG",
              "text": "look: Trace the zip-tie to the service tag.",
              "next": "N230_SHROUD_TAG_NARR"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the bay options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N220_SHROUD_INSTRUMENTS_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "What instruments.",
          "next": "N221_SHROUD_INSTRUMENTS_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N221_SHROUD_INSTRUMENTS_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The label does not list them.\n\nIt assumes you already have them\u2014or that you will be the instrument.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N230_SHROUD_TAG_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A brittle service tag hangs behind the shroud, dated in three different handwriting styles.\n\nThe latest entry is a blank line with a signature box nobody used.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N300_SWEETSPOT_DESC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The floor mark is a rectangle of yellow paint with a stenciled caption: RADIO SWEET-SPOT.\n\nUnder the yellow are older outlines\u2014two previous \u201csweet-spots,\u201d shifted by inches, each crossed out with an X that looks angry for something so minor.",
          "next": "N310_SWEETSPOT_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N310_SWEETSPOT_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_MOVE",
              "text": "ask: Why move it.",
              "next": "N320_SWEETSPOT_MOVE_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_SCUFF",
              "text": "look: Check the scuff pattern.",
              "next": "N330_SWEETSPOT_SCUFF_NARR"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_SHOW_POSTURE",
              "text": "show: Adjust stance to the mark\u2019s centerline (link stability, on paper).",
              "checks": [
                {
                  "type": "skill",
                  "skill": "PROCEDURE",
                  "dc": 11
                }
              ],
              "onPassNext": "N340_SWEETSPOT_POSTURE_PASS",
              "onFailNext": "N341_SWEETSPOT_POSTURE_FAIL"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the bay options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N320_SWEETSPOT_MOVE_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Why move it?",
          "next": "N321_SWEETSPOT_MOVE_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N321_SWEETSPOT_MOVE_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "There\u2019s no note. Just revisions.\n\nThe building records location changes better than reasons.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N330_SWEETSPOT_SCUFF_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The heaviest scuffs are centered exactly where you\u2019re standing.\n\nPeople stood here a lot, and not for comfort.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N340_SWEETSPOT_POSTURE_PASS",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You shift your boots until they align with the oldest outline under the yellow.\n\nThe bay\u2019s quiet changes\u2014subtle, like a system admitting you found the intended place to be.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N341_SWEETSPOT_POSTURE_FAIL",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You adjust, then adjust again.\n\nNothing rewards you. The paint keeps its secrets.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N400_CHUTE_DESC",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The outgoing packet chute is labeled like a mailbox that resents being called a mailbox.\n\nA stack of thin routing slips sits in the throat\u2014pre-punched, pre-numbered, pre-justified.",
          "next": "N410_CHUTE_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N410_CHUTE_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_LOOK_LAST_SLIP",
              "text": "look: Read the last routing slip.",
              "next": "N420_CHUTE_LASTSLIP_NARR"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_USE_FEED_CORRECTION",
              "text": "use: Feed a correction packet.",
              "next": "N430_CHUTE_FEED_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the bay options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N420_CHUTE_LASTSLIP_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The last slip is stamped twice, as if the first stamp wasn\u2019t brave enough.\n\nDESTINATION: OVERFLOW INTAKE\nCLASS: TEMPORARY HOLD\nREASON: CAPACITY MANAGEMENT\n\nThe word \u201ctemporary\u201d is doing most of the work.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N430_CHUTE_FEED_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Correction packet.",
          "next": "N431_CHUTE_FEED_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N431_CHUTE_FEED_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The chute accepts the slip without resistance.\n\nThat is either good design or a willingness to take anything as long as it\u2019s formatted.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N480_CONFIRM_INTRO",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The control recess waits under the shroud: a slot that looks like it was designed for a token, not a hand.\n\nIf you do this, you do it as maintenance. You do it with a paper trail. You do it without inventing verbs you can\u2019t defend.",
          "next": "N490_CONFIRM_MENU"
        },
        {
          "id": "N490_CONFIRM_MENU",
          "type": "player_choice",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "choices": [
            {
              "id": "C_USE_SEND_NOW",
              "text": "use: Insert the token and send the correction packet.",
              "conditions": [
                {
                  "key": "act2.slotTokenCollected",
                  "op": "==",
                  "value": true
                }
              ],
              "next": "N500_COMMIT_PLAYER"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_ASK_BACK",
              "text": "ask: Back to the bay options.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            },
            {
              "id": "C_LEAVE_ABORT",
              "text": "leave: Not yet.",
              "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N590_NO_TOKEN",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You reach for the recess and stop.\n\nWithout the slot token, this isn\u2019t a procedure. It\u2019s a story.\n\nThe bay offers you no help writing it.",
          "next": "N011_REDIRECT_MAIN"
        },
        {
          "id": "N500_COMMIT_PLAYER",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "PLAYER",
          "text": "Reverse route. Maintenance framing.",
          "next": "N501_COMMIT_NARR"
        },
        {
          "id": "N501_COMMIT_NARR",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "You seat the slot token in the control recess. It clicks like a stamp finding its ink.\n\nThe aperture\u2019s surface tightens\u2014subtle, like a muscle remembering it has a job.",
          "next": "N510_RADIO_BLEED"
        },
        {
          "id": "N510_RADIO_BLEED",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "A thin speaker grille above the bay hisses to life.\n\nNot a clean channel. Not even a proper call. Just bleed-through\u2014Earth-side radio fragments caught in the alignment.",
          "next": "N511_RADIO_BUDGET_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "N511_RADIO_BUDGET_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "OLEA_BUDGET",
          "text": "\u2026don\u2019t put \u201creturn\u201d in there. (pause)\nIt\u2019s\u2014 it\u2019s a reversion to the prior state. (pause)\nFunding chases the wording\u2014",
          "next": "N512_RADIO_LEGAL_1"
        },
        {
          "id": "N512_RADIO_LEGAL_1",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "OLEA_LEGAL",
          "text": "\u201cReturn\u201d reads like you left. (pause)\nIf you left then somebody consented. (pause)\nIf somebody consented then somebody reviewed. (pause)\nWe did not\u2014 we\u2019re not on record\u2014 (pause)",
          "next": "N513_RADIO_BUDGET_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N513_RADIO_BUDGET_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "OLEA_BUDGET",
          "text": "I\u2019m not doing verb court. (pause)\nCompletion bonus ties to presence at closure site\u2014 (pause)\nso we define the site as\u2014",
          "next": "N514_RADIO_LEGAL_2"
        },
        {
          "id": "N514_RADIO_LEGAL_2",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "OLEA_LEGAL",
          "text": "Call it \u201coccupied for documentation.\u201d (pause) Don\u2019t put \u201cabandoned\u201d or \u201cleft\u201d in there. (pause) \u201cAbandoned\u201d invites a third party to claim\u2014",
          "next": "N515_RADIO_BUDGET_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "N515_RADIO_BUDGET_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "OLEA_BUDGET",
          "text": "Third party? (pause)\nThere isn\u2019t one. It\u2019s municipal infrastructure. (pause)\nIt\u2019s ours by default\u2014",
          "next": "N516_RADIO_LEGAL_3"
        },
        {
          "id": "N516_RADIO_LEGAL_3",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "OLEA_LEGAL",
          "text": "\u201cBy default\u201d won\u2019t hold up. (pause) Not as chain of title. (pause)\nAnd stop saying \u201cstill.\u201d (pause) \u201cStill operating\u201d reads like we chose. (pause) to keep it\u2014",
          "next": "N517_CUT"
        },
        {
          "id": "N517_CUT",
          "type": "npc_line",
          "speakerId": "NARRATOR",
          "text": "The radio cuts mid-sentence, like someone pulled a plug to prevent a precedent.\n\nThe mirror-surface aperture loses your reflection first.\n\nThen it loses the room.",
          "next": "N520_END_REVERSE_ROUTE"
        },
        {
          "id": "N520_END_REVERSE_ROUTE",
          "type": "end",
          "outcomeId": "reverse_route_to_earth",
          "effects": [
            {
              "key": "story.act",
              "action": "set",
              "value": 3
            },
            {
              "key": "nav.targetScreen",
              "action": "set",
              "value": "HUB-13"
            },
            {
              "key": "act2.completed",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            },
            {
              "key": "knowledge.earthRadioFragmentsHeard",
              "action": "set",
              "value": true
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "id": "N900_END_LEAVE",
          "type": "end"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}